investigation.title: Altered rodent gait characteristics after ~35 days in orbit aboard the International Space Station
investigation.description: The long-term adaptations to microgravity and other spaceflight challenges within the confines of a spacecraft, and readaptations to weight-bearing upon reaching a destination, are unclear. While post-flight gait change in astronauts have been well documented and reflect multi-system deficits, no data from rodents have been collected.

project.title: Exercise Countermeasures for Knee and Hip Joint Degradation during Spaceflight
